-- lib.scroll-card: Actor. Dancer. Dreamer.
id: home
cta-text: Resume
cta-link: $assets.files.assets.resume.pdf
cta-text-2: Headshots
cta-link-2: /
cta-text-3: Introduction Video
cta-link-3: https://youtu.be/ApiSGFC_gpM
small: true

I’m Nikie, an actor trained at FTII. I’ve done theatre with the National
School of Drama and the Sri Ram Centre, played leads in indie films, and
worked on projects for Netflix and Prime Video with directors like Hansal
Mehta, Ashwiny Iyer Tiwari, and Sudhir Mishra.

Dance and movement are a big part of me — I’ve trained in Kathak, Odissi,
Bachata, Kizomba, and Indian martial arts. They’ve taught me rhythm,
discipline, and how to listen with my whole body.

As a person, I’m curious, a little restless, and drawn to stories that cross
borders. My hope is simple: to be part of work that feels alive, honest, and
unforgettable — whether it’s in India or anywhere in the world.

